retest bug 1261814'}, {'account_id': 4257, 'date': '2013-12-17 21:39:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 19: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(3 inline comments)

I am strongly opposed to this hidden dependency stuff. Are you serious that the ExtraRoutes Neutron extension offers no way to update the route table in a non-racy way? If that is the case then Neutron is unequivocally broken, and you should be directing your efforts at fixing it in the first instance.

Implementation options in order of preference:

- Best: Neutron allows routes to be added/deleted individually.
- Good: Neutron detects races (e.g. with ETag/If-Match headers) and rejects them (412 response), allowing us to retry.
- Barely acceptable: Heat models the broken Neutron API (i.e. has a ExtraRoutes route table resource instead of a bunch of Route resources) - sucks for the user but this is Neutron's fault.
- Unacceptable: Cover up the race conditions with hidden dependencies between routes defined in the same stack, ignoring the fact that the whole point of modelling a Route is to allow multiple stacks to contribute routes and yet this is completely unsafe to do."}, {'account_id': 4257, 'date': '2013-12-17 21:42:41.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 19:

BTW we do not run multi-threaded, so handle_create is atomic within the context of it's own stack anyway, with or without the dependencies which are actually achieving nothing. The only race possible is from other stacks or anything else writing to the ExtraRoutes API, and the dependencies do nothing to solve that."}, {'account_id': 7787, 'date': '2013-12-17 22:30:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 19: (1 inline comment)

Zane,

You are right about cross-stack routes being race vulnerable. Steve Baker had said that stack resources were handled in parallel, which is what the current dependency code handles. 


>Best: Neutron allows routes to be added/deleted individually.

This would be ideal, but it will require changes to the neutron API, the neutron client, and all of the plugins that implement this extension so it may be a difficult change to implement for Icehouse. 

>Good: Neutron detects races (e.g. with ETag/If-Match headers) and rejects them (412 response), allowing us to retry.

Setting a precondition requirement in neutron would be a breaking change to any existing API uses that expect to set routes in a single-update operation. 

>Barely acceptable: Heat models the broken Neutron API (i.e. has a ExtraRoutes route table resource instead of a bunch of Route resources) - sucks for the user but this is Neutron's fault.

How does this fix cross-stack races? Also, if this requires the entire route table to be specified by the user, this will not meet the target use case of a stack just adding a route without affecting the others. 

>Unacceptable: Cover up the race conditions with hidden dependencies between routes defined in the same stack, ignoring the fact that the whole point of modelling a Route is to allow multiple stacks to contribute routes and yet this is completely unsafe to do.

I agree. I didn't notice the multi-stack race conditions. I was addressing parallelism in the same stack. 



What if I just use the openstack lockutils (part of the common library) for now on the route methods? It makes it quite clear that we are dealing with a race condition of the neutron API. I know they are frowned upon, but it makes it quite clear what the issue is and it handles it with one line of code."}, {'account_id': 4257, 'date': '2013-12-17 23:13:46.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 19: (1 inline comment)

>You are right about cross-stack routes being race vulnerable. Steve Baker had said that stack resources were handled in parallel, which is what the current dependency code handles.

It's parallel in the sense that anything could happen between handle_create() and check_create_complete(). But there's no context switch to anything in the same user request that can occur inside handle_create().

>>Best: Neutron allows routes to be added/deleted individually.
>This would be ideal, but it will require changes to the neutron API, the neutron client, and all of the plugins that implement this extension so it may be a difficult change to implement for Icehouse.

I tend to agree that this will be hard work to get through, even though it is the best solution. I'm not familiar enough with the Neutron architecture to know if the plugins need to be changed or not. Honestly, if they do it's even more broken than I thought and Neutron folks should be treating this as a top priority.

>>Good: Neutron detects races (e.g. with ETag/If-Match headers) and rejects them (412 response), allowing us to retry.
>Setting a precondition requirement in neutron would be a breaking change to any existing API uses that expect to set routes in a single-update operation.

It's not a breaking change because if you don't supply an If-Match header then the behaviour is the same (but still broken, which is why this is not the ideal solution). This is easily the least-intrusive option IMO.

>>Barely acceptable: Heat models the broken Neutron API (i.e. has a ExtraRoutes route table resource instead of a bunch of Route resources) - sucks for the user but this is Neutron's fault.
>How does this fix cross-stack races? Also, if this requires the entire route table to be specified by the user, this will not meet the target use case of a stack just adding a route without affecting the others.

It doesn't fix it as such, it just forces the user to filter all of their routes down to a single ExtraRoutes resource per router, because that's the only thing that can be supported by the underlying API. I think this is a terrible outcome for the user, but IMO it's better than offering guarantees that we can't actually enforce.

>>Unacceptable: Cover up the race conditions with hidden dependencies between routes defined in the same stack, ignoring the fact that the whole point of modelling a Route is to allow multiple stacks to contribute routes and yet this is completely unsafe to do.
>I agree. I didn't notice the multi-stack race conditions. I was addressing parallelism in the same stack.

Not just cross-stack, the user can cause a race just by legitimately adding/removing routes outside of Heat.

>What if I just use the openstack lockutils (part of the common library) for now on the route methods? It makes it quite clear that we are dealing with a race condition of the neutron API. I know they are frowned upon, but it makes it quite clear what the issue is and it handles it with one line of code.

In Neutron or Heat? The problem cannot be solved in Heat, because the user can independently update the route table and cause a race. (In any event, we are about to introduce multi-engine support for Heat, which IIUC will confound the lockutils solution.) And I don't think this would work in Neutron (no way to match up the read/write requests)."}, {'account_id': 7787, 'date': '2013-12-18 00:09:28.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 19: (1 inline comment)

>I'm not familiar enough with the Neutron architecture to know if the plugins need to be changed or not. Honestly, if they do it's even more broken than I thought and Neutron folks should be treating this as a top priority.

It all depends on the plugin. extraroutes is just an extension that adds a 'routes' list to the router object during router update operations. They aren't  first class citizens in neutron. It may be possible to add calls that safely add/remove a single route while maintaining compatibility with the current method. That will also require updates to the neutron client.

>It's not a breaking change because if you don't supply an If-Match header then the behaviour is the same (but still broken, which is why this is not the ideal solution). This is easily the least-intrusive option IMO.

I see. From my experience, the neutron architecture doesn't expose raw requests information like headers at the level this would need to be implemented at, but it may be possible. Additionally, the neutron client will need to be updated to allow extra header parameters to update_router so this option will require a couple of changes. 


>In Neutron or Heat? The problem cannot be solved in Heat, because the user can independently update the route table and cause a race. (In any event, we are about to introduce multi-engine support for Heat, which IIUC will confound the lockutils solution.) And I don't think this would work in Neutron (no way to match up the read/write requests).

It would be in heat. It would solve the problem of races in heat, but not with outside updates to the routes outside of heat. It will probably break across multiple heat engines too like you pointed out.

Can we just allow the current solution until extra functionality can be added to neutron to handle safe adds/deletes?"}, {'account_id': 4257, 'date': '2013-12-18 01:39:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 19: (1 inline comment)

The ETag/If-Match thing should be pretty easy to implement in the API. The ETag can just be a hash of the route table. When you get a PUT with If-Match set, just grab the current route table and hash it to compare before proceeding. The only tricky part is making this atomic, but lockutils could be an option there.

Obviously this will require client changes too, but they should be reasonably trivial.

I'm more open to accepting this without fixing Neutron than I was when I thought it involved the dependency hackery, but I'm still concerned that we are offering an apparent guarantee that the underlying implementation cannot support. "Let's just get this in" is not necessarily a bad idea, but often it really means "let's just never fix it".'}, {'account_id': 8641, 'date': '2013-12-22 04:15:16.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 19: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

commit_message:
Adds extraroutes support to neutron routers

Adds a RouterExtraRoutes Neutron resource to allow
extra routes to be added to a neutron router that
supports the extra routes extension.

Implements: blueprint router-properties-object
Change-Id: Ie35213a507a5b8dd1061a6a7ea220b3a1bdb3ec6

commit_message:
Configuration agent for Cisco Service VMs

A generic config agent for configuring L3 services in Cisco devices,
including service VMs.

Implements blueprint: cisco-config-agent
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/neutron/+spec/cisco-config-agent

Change-Id: If230194f544281131a61c706a7f7c70bdd6c29b6

commit_message:
NSX: allow replication_mode to be configurable

This patch allows the replication mode in nsx to be configurable via devstack.
This is useful for testing as setting to source allows one to use nsx without
having to deploy a service node.

Change-Id: I88da49e0ab415f06cb5a218f921149dbfb7c6f2e

commit_message:
VMware vSphere support: Disk rates

1) Implemented pollsters for following disk rate counters
   - disk.read.bytes.rate
   - disk.read.requests.rate
   - disk.write.bytes.rate
   - disk.write.requests.rate

2) Extended the 'virt.inspector' to return the disk rate stats via
'inspect_disk_rates()'. As of now only vmware.inspector implements this
method.

3) Wrote test cases for the newly added disk rate pollsters and
inspect_disk_rates().

Change-Id: I1089b708ae3b651c95013129dbc0129b419d2b62
Implements: blueprint vmware-vcenter-server

commit_message:
Provide explicit image create value in Registry v2 API test

Assign an explicit created_at datetime value to image db fixtures,
it be used to fixes race condition in Registry v2 API test cases.

Closes-Bug: #1279753
Change-Id: Ia1957e8c024f81eeaa3c0bc094dd62db1be52d07
Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>

A space in the command construction was being caught by the
ssh-injection check. The fix is to separate the command strings.

Change-Id: If1f719f9c2ceff31ed5386c53cf60bc7f522f4d7
Closes-Bug: #1280409

commit_message:
Fixes ssh-injection error while using chap authentication

A space in the command construction was being caught by the
ssh-injection check. The fix is to separate the command strings.

Change-Id: If1f719f9c2ceff31ed5386c53cf60bc7f522f4d7
Closes-Bug: #1280409

commit_message:
Query for port before calling l3plugin.disassociate_floatingips()

The call to l3plugin.disassociate_floatingips() trigggers several events
that could cause a timeout to occur trying to query the db for the port
therefore this patch changes the code to query first for the port.

Closes-bug: #1290478

Change-Id: I69fe9cff4b550240215329e1082a63cd11617faa

commit_message:
remove distros that are out of support by their upstream

raring EOL was - 27 Jan 2014
f18 EOL was - 14 Jan 2014
opensuse 12.2 was - 15 Jan 2014

if their upstream isn't going to support them, we shouldn't be
in devstack.

this additionally leaves us in an interesting situation that there
is no longer *any* opensuse version listed as supported. if the
opensuse community doesn't step up here we should probably look
at removing it.

Change-Id: Ibb883930b430477dfd3b5126c5db04f95a50d3a7

dean,

like this.'}, {'account_id': 970, 'date': '2014-03-06 15:37:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me (core reviewer)

regarding third party stuff in devstack in general,
probably it's a good idea to document what uses which thirdparty stuff
somewhere.
eg. ryu is for ryu plugin
eg. trema is for nec plugin  (this one is not obvious.)"}, {'account_id': 970, 'date': '2014-03-07 04:44:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Stop running setup_devel for Ryu

It doesn't work here for various reasons.
- Ryu's setup.py is incompatible with global requirements
- This code is called before install_infra.

Ryu is not a part of OpenStack anyway.

Closes-Bug: 1287569
Change-Id: I01a942411f7d06bdf8f1fec5d1a0bc319560f329

commit_message:
Adds basic Marconi test

This patch adds the config options needed to add Queuing tests.
This patch also has a basic test to verify that everything works
as expected.

Implements: blueprint add-basic-marconi-tests

commit_message:
Call target plugin out of DB transaction in the Metaplugin

Previously, there are cases that a target plugin is called
within a DB transaction in the metaplugin. This possibly causes
"DB lock timeout" error since a target plugin may take a long
time (ex. communicate to a controller).

Change-Id: Ie2971bfae1fecc97086b58cd943c321feb0aba04
Closes-Bug: #1267291

subject: NSX: Add ability to retry on 503's returned by the controller

commit_message:
NSX: Add ability to retry on 503's returned by the controller

There are a number of circumstances where the NSX controller
may return 503. Currently the API client does not retry, so
this patch adds a retry logic with timeout.

Closes-bug: #1284277

Change-Id: I85df087d5ae409e6cb5c35eb171e89346abe81f4

commit_message:
Added warnings regarding networking updates for Icehouse

I added several warnings informing users about potential structure
and/or content issues during the update process for Icehouse. I will
remove these warnings after we complete the process.

Change-Id: Ic13fbbdf60005d5e87ce90e7f3eb225e7e5d5698
Partial-Bug: #1291071

[{'created': '2014-03-10 15:25:12.000000000', 'message': 'Fix baremetal flavor image size

When storing the node details in the JSON datafile, the DISK size
was incremented for baremetal nodes creation and store after that,
so the baremetal flavor was created with a root disk size bigger
than expected.

Closes-Bug: #1290399
Change-Id: Idc6a3d4f89badeeffb2e17ac84e10cbfa3629de6
'}]
commit_message:
Fix baremetal flavor image size

When storing the node details in the JSON datafile, the DISK size
was incremented for baremetal nodes creation and store after that,
so the baremetal flavor was created with a root disk size bigger
than expected.

Closes-Bug: #1290399
Change-Id: Idc6a3d4f89badeeffb2e17ac84e10cbfa3629de6

commit_message:
Changes for networking metrics support for vSphere

Added pollsters to poll network bytes transferred rates from VMware
Vsphere inspector.

Change-Id: Icea673381cc3cdc5e177db23846d301eb398f53e
Implements: blueprint vmware-vcenter-server

commit_message:
put libvirt debug behind a flag

only turn on the libvirt debugging if we really need it, which
we could control in the gate via devstack-gate.

Change-Id: I5e6d41d5333357608ab6a614610c060400f70a10

commit_message:
Ignore H302 as other TripleO projects

Ignore H302 "Do not import objects, only modules" rule.

This is in accordance with other TripleO projects and will allow
e.g. importing the translation function `_`.

Change-Id: I5c27d77334a1e75318302d6330cf1a0c670a940a

commit_message:
Add missing swift constraint for functional tests

Looks like we are keeping at least four lists of the default
constraints in various places, and when we added the max_header_size
in initial Static Large Object Support commit (5d73da15) we failed to
add it to the two locations in the test tree (test/sample.conf and
test/functional/tests.py).

With this commit we take a small step to consolidate the list of
constraints to the constraints module by removing the list from the
tests module (note we still have them listed in the sample swift.conf
file and the test module's sample.conf file), document the missing
reference in the test module's sample.conf file, and, while we're at
it, use the SWIFT_CONF_FILE reference where possible.

Change-Id: Ic4fa5f1aedec9bc7a7b43ce1a2ca3cdebce6171f

commit_message:
libvirt: fix blockinfo get_device_name helper

Currently all the methods in libvirt's blockinfo module will either
be called with block device objects (when attempting to default device
names)  or with a DriverBlockDevice subclass (all other operations in
the virt driver that expect such format to be passed).

This patch updates the get_device_name method to honor the above
situation introduced by I055651b5fd415092787d9487a69467a9bbcf073e.

Closes-bug: #1290302

commit_message:
TCP port is appended two time in ClientException

urlparse netloc contains the TCP port if presents.
There is no need to provide conn.port when building
CLientException.

Change-Id: Id3e4fa8c4f4ab2ad693b0e8702ab69ed7c291830

commit_message:
Client support for export and import backup service metadata

Add client code to a new admin API for backup-export and
backup-import allowing an admin to copy the backup metadata
details.

client code for https://review.openstack.org/#/c/69351/

blueprint cinder-backup-recover-api
DocImpact new admin API calls backup-import and backup-export

Change-Id: Id306fc9cf562a87bb6a36eae692852eefc592b74

commit_message:
Add missing documentation for enabling oauth1 auth plugin

The oauth1 method and plugin must be declared in keystone.conf for
OS-OAUTH1 to be completely enabled.

Change-Id: I23b479d3cd462ea3823dee0c281a26486f8600ac
Closes-Bug: #1290966

Despite the existence of the deprecation plan, I do not see the value of removing this code. I have been sprinting for 2 months to make this work and have contributed a number of fixes and improvements both into Nova and into Tempest. I have stood up the CI servers. No, they are not yet enabled, although we're incredibly close, and yes we have missed the deadline. I do not argue there has not been fair warning, nor that the removal is unfair. Instead, I argue that it is unnecessary.

This driver is far from unmaintained and it works. It is not a maintenance burden. There is nothing to be lost here by changing the warning into something appropriate to indicate that it is a new driver with limited testing. There are no significant flaws in the driver that are requiring this removal, only a lack of CI, which while serious in itself, is something that could be safely addressed during the stable release. There are, as I see it, only disadvantages to moving this code out of Nova.

This is not a "HyperV moment" where threat of removal is going to spur forces into action.

How much time is going to be wasted by moving this code to stackforge? Manipulating devstack into installing and using this new driver? Into adjusting our current CI work to match these changes? Into reverting it all with moving the code back into Nova? Will we still have the resources to devote to adding missing API functionality, Cinder and Neutron support?

No, I disagree with this patch.'}, {'account_id': 2750, 'date': '2014-03-11 20:18:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Looks good to me (core reviewer)

This isn't about "punishing" docker, this is about ensuring a high quality for our users. CI is important, and we need to drag the drivers forward into a better tested universe. commit_message:
Remove the docker driver

The docker compute driver does not currently have CI running against
it.  In accordance with our plan to require this for all drivers, we
are now removing the driver from nova.

https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/HypervisorSupportMatrix/DeprecationPlan

At this point, the driver should be set up in a stackforge repository
and have CI staged from there to prove its reliability before we could
consider bringing it back into Nova.

DocImpact
UpgradeImpact

Change-Id: I1c9bea2fdeebc4199c4f7d8fca4580a6fb7fed5b

[{'created': '2014-02-17 21:13:42.000000000', 'message': 'VPNaaS Device Driver for Cisco CSR

This is the device driver for the vendor specific VPNaaS plugin. This
change relies on the service driver code (review 74144) and Service
Type Framework (client 53602 and server 41827) all out for review.

Open items on this first pathset:
- There is still some refactoring needed in the reporting/syncing code
- Handling of service delete clean-up
- Failure handling (agent restart, RPC failure,...)
- Future: Sharing/tracking of policies (will do if time allows, but
  have workaround in the meantime).
- Update/create Tempest tests to run 3rd party tests for this.

Note: To run, this needs an out-of-band Cisco CSR installed and
      configured.
Note: This uses a newer version of requests library and a new httmock
      library. Need guidance on how to include these.

Change-Id: I4f73f7fa1bfcdc89a35ffe63dd253f8eede98485
Paritally-Implements: blueprint vpnaas-cisco-driver

commit_message:
VPNaaS Device Driver for Cisco CSR

This is the device driver for the vendor specific VPNaaS plugin. This
change relies on the service driver code (review 74144), which is also
out for review.

Note: Support for sharing of IKE/IPSec policies (which is currently
      prevented by the service driver code), will be done as a later
      enhancement.
Note: Needs Tempest tests updated/created to test this.
Note: To run, this needs an out-of-band Cisco CSR installed and
      configured.
Note: This uses a newer version of requests library and a new httmock
      library. Until these are approved (75296), the UT will be
      renamed to prevent testing the REST client API to the CSR.

Change-Id: I4f73f7fa1bfcdc89a35ffe63dd253f8eede98485
Paritally-Implements: blueprint vpnaas-cisco-driver

commit_message:
Run overcloud deploy tests against the seed.

Currently we deploy the overcloud on the undercloud, but there is no
conceptual benefit to this - the undercloud is meant to be tested
entirely via the undercloud test; the seed is the same code as the
undercloud, differing only in the use of static configuration rather
than heat delivered configuration. Avoiding the undercloud
build-and-deploy makes the overcloud test substantially faster.

Change-Id: Id5895be09ad6728f9d83d260371d02777ee217e8

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-03-11 09:12:02.000000000', 'message': "Add constraint to sg rule's remote_ip_prefix

When create or update rules, there is no constraint to remote_ip_prefix,
we can give invalid value such as '--'.

Change-Id: I8c28e814ce6585ff0d9163ad78860a0d0ea39590
Closes-Bug: #1290269
"}]
commit_message:
Add constraint to sg rule's remote_ip_prefix

When create or update rules, there is no constraint to remote_ip_prefix,
we can give invalid value such as '--'.

Change-Id: I8c28e814ce6585ff0d9163ad78860a0d0ea39590
Closes-Bug: #1290269

commit_message:
Add TaskManager lock on change port data

Updating port data may require driver actions on the related node
(if address changed for example). New method 'update_port' added
to conductor manager and rpcapi.

Partial-Bug: #1276393
Related-Bug: #1236714
Change-Id: I1f817a8b3c80630f40fd36c82e533d5358225150

commit_message:
Resource type implementations for structured software config

StructuredConfig takes configuration as a Map property, which
results in config that is stored and returned as a parsed dict.

This will be used for defining both cfn-init and tripleo software
configuration inline in a template as strucured yaml.

StructuredSoftwareDeployment will transform the config to substitute
{"get_input": "<input_name>"} with the current input values and storing
the result in the ephemeral derived config.

partial blueprint hot-software-config

Change-Id: I8029f469dfc2a77453abdab46c1a69ba317fc7ea

commit_message:
Configurable temporary directory for tests

The temporary directory used for testing was always
keystone/tests/tmp. This change makes it so that the temporary
directory can be configured by setting the KEYSTONE_TEST_TEMP_DIR
environment variable. For example:

 $ mkdir ~/keystone_test_temp
 $ sudo mount -t tmpfs -o size=16M tmpfs ~/keystone_test_temp &&
    sudo chown $USER: ~/keystone_test_temp
 $ KEYSTONE_TEST_TEMP_DIR=$HOME/keystone_test_temp tox -e py27

Change-Id: I41f86a23882a382ab19747e008720c0da5fd56e6

commit_message:
Fix broken statistics in sqlalchemy

When querying the samples for statistics calculations,
the filtering is done without joining the Sample table.
This patch fixes this.

Closes-Bug: #1289325
Change-Id: I45edc974a6c054d27ac33d5287f760bcff08cf91

commit_message:
Use  a instance lookup helper to v3 plugins

Since I52c15da0499eda676225603d5a0b2739875d1fca, common get_instance() has
been added, the method would make API behaviors consistent.
This patch applies the method to ips and server_diagnostics plugins.

Change-Id: I23c58c43ac9075cedd80b7543ddf8a102d9ee4d5

commit_message:
List filesystem and swift as known glance stores

Glance used to default to include all stores as "known" but has now
switched to only knowing the filesystem store by default. As of
I82073352641d3eb2ab3d6e9a6b64afc99a30dcc7

Change-Id: I10aebbd7c6969c6d95579f3b266e03501a7bedb7
Closes-Bug: #1290969

commit_message:
Use upstream/package keystone-paste.ini.

We have an old, out of date keystone-paste.ini file that isn't needed
for templating. This change will ensure that we have the latest from
upstream.

Change-Id: Ifae28a1f25dab0974dfc352108f8e23e362ce34e

commit_message:
Make some plan types mandatory

This makes artifact_type, requirement_type and service reference id mandatory
It does not make sense to create these objects without the types.

Change-Id: I226b136d5b1844b4d2781bbab2c3c27d8a39a4b6

in certificate functions for BigSwitch plugin.

commit_message:
Generic MixinVendorInterface using static mapping

Use a MixinVendorInterface and a dict for static mapping,
so every method:vendor interface mapping is explicit.

Example:

self.pxe_vendor = pxe.VendorPassthru()
self.ipmi_vendor = ipminative.VendorPassthru()
self.mapping = {'pass_deploy_info': self.pxe_vendor,
	        'set_boot_device': self.ipmi_vendor}
self.vendor = utils.MixinVendorInterface(self.mapping)

Partial-Bug: #1264596

Change-Id: I5dd5a02164670476b0d6ff121bed57569c341a61

commit_message:
Add plan manager and corresponding tests

For m1 we are converting plan yaml file into json. This can be modified to use
yaml itself once we have support for yaml in API layer.

Change-Id: I96f986dde059d66633cbc24797a89619ea5bf52e

commit_message:
Add solum builder client

This client will be used to communicate with builder service from solum.

Generalize KeystoneAuthPlugin so that it can be used by both solumclient and
builder client.

Fixed a bug in solumclient/common/base.py

Change-Id: I86630f40b32c6fcada5aa292fae8e36cecab9908

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-03-11 01:14:59.000000000', 'message': "Destroy all ci testenv domains

Leaving these running with IP's from previous test runs may cause IP
conflicts and end up in errors booting new instances in ci runs.

Ideally this wouldn't live in boot-seed-vm but its where we currently

commit_message:
Destroy all testenv domains

Leaving these running with IP's from previous test runs may cause IP
conflicts and end up in errors booting new instances in devtest runs.
Killing these vm's is only needed while using nova-baremetal as ironic
will assert their state.

Ideally this wouldn't live in boot-seed-vm but its where we currently
kill the seed so it makes sense to keep it together.

Change-Id: I591775f85169d1c454373b19d3a66ba80bf818d3

commit_message:
Update translation setup for cli-reference

The propose_translation_update_manual job did not work since
we needed to initialize some files for it first. I expect that this
fixes the job.

I updates the transifex config to know about cli-refernece and creates
the pot file.

Related-Bug: #1275599
Change-Id: Ib6544fa7545722d61115224a1bb0e51b7ce7c272

commit_message:
Add missing documentation for enabling federation auth plugin

The saml2 method and plugin must be declared in keystone.conf for
federation to be completely enabled.

Change-Id: Id68ffdc8a84d093406c836ee6988bfdb9e58d50f
Closes-Bug: #1290582
Co-Authored-By: Florent Flament <florent.flament-ext@cloudwatt.com>

commit_message:
Task cleanup_running_deleted_instances can now use slave

Deployments that have a slave_connection configured can offload
read queries generated by this periodic task there. For
deployments with no slave, behavior remains the same.

Partially-implements: blueprint periodic-tasks-to-db-slave
Change-Id: Ie1e6cdfbefab096a2af62ef636786a5c8f659b13

commit_message:
Expose clients directly from osclients.Clients

* Lazy load client handles instead of eager instantiation.
* Update all client handle references to use osclients.Clients.

Change-Id: Iffd17eb37886ca07190d1e2fbb6c02ff6081f69a

Generate config samples for oslo.messaging

commit_message:
Conductor logs better error if seamicroclient missing

If the driver is installed and the python entrypoint discoverable, but
the external library is not present, the conductor will log exceptions
during startup and remove the *_seamicro drivers from the list of
drivers it advertises support for.

This patch tests the imports and raises one DriverNotFound error for
each affected driver if python-seamicroclient is not installed, instead
of raising several ImportErrors.

This also removes python-seamicroclient from requirements.txt

Change-Id: I5cde3c3e8c7cbc2bf4991c0ed390ac655dcdbc7c

commit_message:
Add depends_on key to dependency resolution

The depends_on key was being ignored when calculating resource
dependencies. This patch adds support for the depends_on HOT
keyword.

Change-Id: I7b1dcd841b3491506c9924b59728a1512a6432b7
Closes-Bug: 1288997

commit_message:
Use oslo's config generator to generate sample

This patch adds oslo's config generator to the source tree and uses it
to generate marconi's sample configs. It also adds a check to pep8 that
verifies the config file is up-to-date.

Change-Id: Iec7defa244dc8649a5c832bb81b9ec6f30f0ee37

commit_message:
Prepare Marconi to support oslo's config.generator

This patch removes the options_iter function and prepares marconi's code
base to play nice with oslo's config.generator. The replacement of lists
with tuples is necessary to avoid oslo's config.generator to parse the
globally defined options. In Marconi's case, we want it to use the
registered entry_points. (This is a workaround).

Change-Id: I56995fe16cd0b6e092b522dac3c32e4ec75bb269

commit_message:
Add an options module to sqlalchemy

Let sqla follow the pattern used in other storage drivers. This patch
adds a new options module with a function used by the oslo.config.opts
namespace in the entry_point section.

Change-Id: I0e8b24d7de220104cf59c09883415ae8c5bed8f6

commit_message:
Ensure stop_nova stops nova-objectstore.

Currently, n-obj is not shutdown with the other services in stop_nova.
This adds it to the list of nova services stopped, ensuring it can be
reliably restarted later.

Change-Id: I49dc04983a59047bddab96db569240cb20136afb

commit_message:
Disable file injection by default

File injection in libvirt is problematic in havana on some systems.
When doing a live upgrade where the system suddenly gains libguestfs
support, a compute node may start using it, and thus start breaking.

Related master branch patch: I5015f2c351b1d680c205d7f9a5204febca490b91

When attaching an NFS or GlusterFS volume, nova mounts the share so it
can be reused by other instances but it is not unmounted when detaching.

commit_message:
Unmount the NFS and GlusterFS shares on detach

When attaching an NFS or GlusterFS volume, nova mounts the share so it
can be reused by other instances but it is not unmounted when detaching.

This patch adds the disconnect_volume method to both drivers, which will
try to unmount the share. If a volume in that share is still being used
by another instance, the umount command will fail with the error 'target
is busy' and we will ignore it. Any other error while unmounting will be
properly logged. In any case the detach will fail because nova hasn't
been able to unmount the share.

Closes-Bug: #1285209
Change-Id: I79289524541a88ad359b3465719055cd402b4e3d

commit_message:
Set storage engine for the trait_type table

Not setting the storage engine for this table can cause problems in
those MySQL installations whose default storage engine is not InnoDB.

Change-Id: Ifd0ed0ce7698eb840da87e3f393cd223dcfd36e1
Closes-Bug: #1288894

commit_message:
Refactor tempest's share-network-provider method

This method creates suitable network for tenant,
that will be used in share-network for service VM.

For now there is no creation of network, and we gets
fail if no proper network exists.

Change-Id: I90e57eb0dfb47da754b39df90ea7e2e27293e2e5

commit_message:
Added handling of Unauthorized exception for tempest plugin

clear_resources method tries to release resources
and it should not raise exceptions if resource is
already deleted or client unauthorized to delete.

Change-Id: Ic45d17a4ad62872212401c81f00e0ee700a6dadc

commit_message:
Fix _start_build

- Add a test for start_build
- pass the context into image.save()
- use Popen instead of check_output (to support py2.6)

Change-Id: I8d63b1034f623ffa60906946ce7889d68a7ebbb6

commit_message:
Make config generator function with the duplicate options

If duplicate options are present in the same group, the generator
doesn't properly generate the options.

This patch changes ordering of config options.  It orders based upon
default section, followed by alphabetical ordering by group name.

Within each section, options are ordered alphabetically.

Change-Id: If98d762d592572a1aedb3ba52a55352ca48e567e
Closes-bug: 1288586

commit_message:
Add Storage Policy Support to ssync

This patch makes ssync policy aware and adds plumbing required
for existing test cases to pass as well as required tests to
assure policy support coverage.

commit_message:
ensure => absent must remove the mon data dir

Instead of moving it to another directory because it prevents running
three or more mon installation / destruction in sequence on the same
machine.

Change-Id: I418c2fdcd35ff0bc1cc258d069516f870807cdbe
Signed-off-by: Loic Dachary <loic@dachary.org>

commit_message:
Revert "Don't enable all stores by default"

This reverts commit 1f6381a73f5c99f1f731d6c4f9defb91bd2d042d

The reverted change will break all users of glance with swift backends on upgrade, as this changes the default.

Closes-Bug: #1290969

commit_message:
Don't enable all stores by default

Glance currently enables all stores by default. This patch changes that
by removing all stores that require manual configuration and leaving
those that work right out of the box.

Current behavior causes a lot of confusion to users since most of those
stores print errors when they're not configured correctly. All extra
stores should be enabled explicitly by users.

This fix makes tests use http locations. All other locations besides the
default ones should be tested in their own test suites.

DocImpact
Closes-bug: #1255556
Change-Id: I82073352641d3eb2ab3d6e9a6b64afc99a30dcc7

commit_message:
Add instructions for "normal" user creation

Added instructions for adding a "normal" user named "demo" with access
to the dashboard but no administrative functions. Restructured the
section into procedures to support this and make the task split
clearer.

Change-Id: Iebfec133e44447fad2149ea815c749468b57c763
Closes-Bug: #1266391

commit_message:
Correct iso8601 parseing invalid year num

iso8601 should raise reasonable error when parsing timestamp with invalid
years. This is implemented in iso8601 version 0.1.9.
More details please see the bug description and the issue on bitbucket.

Change-Id: I23ec6a125110294f49eb55ced02ff4e5965a0b99
Closes-Bug: #1266398

commit_message:
Separate action and creation tests in tempest

Update of tempest plugin to separate share tests,
that:
1) cover functionality of creation/deletion
2) cover functionality of actions over entities

Change-Id: I0738c2bc0d07f9450b3fd22756766767cbfdb13a

commit_message:
Use a colon instead of a . in setup.cfg

Mistakenly, the commit that added the oslo.config.opts entry_points used
a `.` before the final function instead of a `:`. This commit fixes
that.

Change-Id: I305cfe9067640bb91ce30e5f13c540931de800a6

commit_message:
Sync from oslo-incubator

This patch is intended to bring in `config.generator`. It also syncs
Marconi's modules to the latest oslo-incubator version for the sake of
being up-to-date.

Change-Id: I9cd3ccf0ce509349d561132025add42dec83ca0a

commit_message:
Update Fibre Channel Zone Manager config documentation

This patch updates block storage config reference documentation
by adding a section describing Fibre Channel Zone Manager and
Brocade Fibre Channel Zone Driver configuration details.

Change-Id: I315b92f10b7b6cb63046fa9c377cdce191450cea
Closes-Bug: #1284993

commit_message:
Add tempest test for heat resource OS::Nova::KeyPair

The template will create two OS::Nova::KeyPair and will test that:
   [*] The key with save_private_key flag set to true outputs both
       public and private keys.
   [*] The key with save_private_key flag set to false outputs
       only the public key.

Testing other cases will require to recreate the stack and
include a negative test case.

Change-Id: I751a85e0efd997a1238c53d8802ebdd8b551e7aa
Partial-Bug: #1271995

commit_message:
fix(cli): Print statement in global error handler

This is the last place we could be writing to stderr from our code. It
seems unlikely this is the root cause of the devstack issue, since our
monkey-patch test should have turned this up, but let's remove it to
be absolutely certain.

Change-Id: Id454d9affcf060d5308f965e25119693ec790624
Partial-Bug: #1287490

commit_message:
Make the path in neutron.conf configurable

Make the path in neutron.conf configurable, in some cases like
if we want to use this cookbook's template to support installation
of neutron agent on windows platform.

commit_message:
Add MySQL-python as a dependency

This is required for the sqlalchemy driver. We can argue whether it is
needed as a default dependency or completely optional but as of now, I'd
recommend having it as a hard dependency and relaxing it later.

Change-Id: I43df1e9f7386888a354119b659d4de3bc69d3b46

commit_message:
Support passing 'neutron_insecure' to neutronclient

When using a self-signed certificate for the network service endpoint,
the metadata agent has to pass the 'insecure' flag to neutronclient.
Otherwise requests will fail due to the failed certificate validity
check.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1269740
Change-Id: I091b1620ab60184921cc12e038af5d717d4d476f

commit_message:
Fix unnecessary error messages in log

Currently if you are working in an environment that cannot reach the
target openstack-ppa uri/components,say you do not have internet access
for instance, you will see an error in the log which is captured in
the refferenced bug report.

By adding a new flag attribute:
['openstack']['apt']['live_updates_enabled'], the opnstack ppa update
can be disabled by setting this attribute to false.

This patch intended to avoid executing an unnesessary code path by
checking the new flag  prior to attempting to fetch updates.

Closes-Bug: #1289356
Change-Id: Ifca7c77e7a84834b88600c14d5a45cc0a64825f8

commit_message:
Adds https support for metadata agent

Adds two configure options to support https client for metadata proxy
* auth_insecure: turn off verification of the certificate for ssl, or
* auth_ca_cert: CA cert to check against with for ssl.

Change-Id: I3ffb86ae9ce31931436a4e13957aae30eebf9d92
Closes-Bug: #1263872

commit_message:
Make ceilometer work with sqla 0.9.x

Ceilometer's migration 028 makes some very specific assumptions
about sqla data structures and exception paths, which are not
true in sqla 0.9.x. In 0.8 you were shielded from errors on drop
by sqla, but in 0.9 you get raw exceptions from the db layer
thrown all the way up, which causes a failure condition when
trying to delete the non existent alembic table.

We can get basically the same behavior as before by using the
checkfirst=True parameter on table definitions. This will
actually ensure that we get the table in question, and get the
NoSuchTableError when we expect it.

Change-Id: Ida33a3030fb03c2f3eeed9f129fcc0063a7b7c4b

Recent pyOpenSSL releases when installed from pip depend on

commit_message:
Use the python-pyOpenSSL package openSUSE

Recent pyOpenSSL releases when installed from pip depend on
cryptography>=0.2.1, which itself depends on cffi>=0.8. That is conflicting
with the python-cffi (0.7.2) package on openSUSE-13.1 which is required by the
installed python-xattr.

Change-Id: I721ce5288d150a3b01fb2558f7ca86028d734138

commit_message:
Delete ERROR+DELETING VMs during compute startup.

We should perhaps do this check during message bus reconnection as
well.. Anyhow, if a compute node is offline during a nova API call
to delete an instance, and the rabbit message is lost for some
reason (or alternatively if the delete method throws an error)
then the task state is not cleared and won't be cleared on compute
restart, leaving it wedged forever.

Change-Id: Ie0a47958eb0fb58307902437a95634d5f54f74f3
Fixes-bug: #1281324
Co-Authored-By: Steve Kowalik <steven@wedontsleep.org>

commit_message:
fix test when unshelve instance that uses wrong image

The bug 1257594 has been reported when unshelve an instance
that uses the wrong image.

A fix on Nova has been pushed:
   https://review.openstack.org/#/c/72407/

Change-Id: Id18f5c5a19dd696a00a04f04f178f3e4c95d3cbf
Closes-Bug: #1257594

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-03-11 08:03:16.000000000', 'message': "remove rspec-system dependencies from Gemfile

rspec-system will fail to install on jenkins slaves. It does not matter
anyway since it is not going to be used for unit tests. Create a
Gemfile-rspec-system to be used when running integration tests. Although
it would be convenient to be able to

   BUNDLE_GEMFILE=Gemfile-rspec-system bundle exec rake spec:system

it will fail because the environment variable won't be propagated where
it should.

   .rspec_system/vagrant_projects/x64/Gemfile-rspec-system not found

The README.md file is updated to simply mv to Gemfile which is good
enough for the environment running the integration tests.

A bug was filed against openstack-ci to resolve this installation
problem but it is unclear if and how it could be fixed
https://bugs.launchpad.net/openstack-ci/+bug/1290710

Change-Id: I0bff624892837536419bdbdd6651b009600fe9c6
Signed-off-by: Loic Dachary <loic@dachary.org>
"}]
commit_message:
remove rspec-system dependencies from Gemfile

rspec-system will fail to install on jenkins slaves. It does not matter
anyway since it is not going to be used for unit tests. Create a
Gemfile-rspec-system to be used when running integration tests. Although
it would be convenient to be able to

   BUNDLE_GEMFILE=Gemfile-rspec-system bundle exec rake spec:system

it will fail because the environment variable won't be propagated where
it should.

   .rspec_system/vagrant_projects/x64/Gemfile-rspec-system not found

The README.md file is updated to simply mv to Gemfile which is good
enough for the environment running the integration tests.

A bug was filed against openstack-ci to resolve this installation
problem but it is unclear if and how it could be fixed
https://bugs.launchpad.net/openstack-ci/+bug/1290710

Change-Id: I0bff624892837536419bdbdd6651b009600fe9c6
Signed-off-by: Loic Dachary <loic@dachary.org>

commit_message:
Factor out _update_db_object method in handlers

The update method is now moved to the db object.
That way, if solum is accessed by something else than the
handlers, it still works fine

Closes bug 1282616
https://bugs.launchpad.net/solum/+bug/1282616

Change-Id: I90430588c666a1d5c8ea6801c92facb059f47296

commit_message:
Hide date picker fields in Resources Usage Overview by default

Date picker fields (From, To) in Admin > Resources Usage Overview panel
should be visible only when "Other" is selected in Period drop down. Since
when the panel loads the default drop down selection is "Last week" these
date picker fields should be hidden by default. This patch fixes the issue
where these fields are displayed very briefly when the panel loads and then
are hidden.

Closes-Bug: #1280423

Change-Id: Iffdcec2c0c957f768f7e9331041a898c61cb2ef3

commit_message:
Add Cinder tests for quota sets

This commit adds client for the Cinder quota API and adds
tests to list and update the quotas.

Change-Id: Ic53dbf6e6ef26c4275039091fc4db6a63f796dba
Closes-Bug: #1252774

commit_message:
Fix ml2 db migration of subnetroutes table

The ml2 db migration path doesn't create subnetroutes table. Therefore
installations were partially relying on automatic schema generation.

This patch fixes the migration path.

Change-Id: I3060dd9538b629ad7277af28008ddde27926dcc4
Closes-Bug: #1290255

VMware vSphere: Changes for cpu_util

Added a pollster to poll CPU_Util from VMware Vsphere inspector.

Change-Id: Ibbfce0dd2ef5175f84a9b901a4653da8dca9c8b2
Implements: blueprint vmware-vcenter-server

I have some concerns about introducing a new pollster the libvirt inspector doesn't support. I think kvm/libvirt is the de facto default for most of the openstack deployment. Running the pollster on libvirt will only procude exception log messages.

I'm wondering if we should also make the libvirt inspector support this, though I'm not sure whether it's possible.

I'm not blocking this, just want to hear more thought."}, {'account_id': 9562, 'date': '2014-03-06 15:52:17.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 11:

Hi Lianhao,

In my opinion, it would be better to have an additional column in the Measurements section to include the information that which meter is supported by which hypervisor rather than blocking the collection of the available data.

In case of libvirt it is a periodically appearing topic, the latest BP regarding to this is quite new: https://blueprints.launchpad.net/ceilometer/+spec/ceilometer-memory-utilization. According to my last check, the memory utilization is kind of calculable in libvirt now from the available counters. I'm not sure about the versions, but as for long term, I assume it will be available for libvirt in OpenStack too.

Best Regards,
Ildiko"}, {'account_id': 6537, 'date': '2014-03-06 16:44:46.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 11:

hmm... i believe it's unavoidable that we'll have gaps between the drivers... i don't think libvirt will ever be a superset of all drivers... the best we can do is support the metrics each driver provides.

that said, looking at logs, i do find it strange that we see memory.usage errors... are the gates not run against kvm only? why do we see vsphere inspector logs?

commit_message:
VMware vSphere support: Memory Usage

1) Added vSphere Hypervisor inspector.
2) Implemented memory usage pollster to generate memory usage samples
for vSphere VMs.

Change-Id: I2aab2fdbc9d0ff4ccf8553bac19c44e463e6595a
Implements: blueprint vmware-vcenter-server

commit_message:
Added option for test of transient cluster

setuptools 3.0 removed the Feature class which breaks at least the cffi
project. cffi is indirectly needed by nova. Keep setuptools 2.2 until cffi is
fixed.

https://bitbucket.org/pypa/setuptools/issue/65
https://bitbucket.org/cffi/cffi/issue/139/

Change-Id: I166aa679bcec79afdaf013b8f393957f849d4daf
'}]
commit_message:
Block setuptools 3.0 to workaround a cffi bug

setuptools 3.0 removed the Feature class which breaks at least the cffi
project. cffi is indirectly needed by nova. Keep setuptools 2.2 until cffi is
fixed.

https://bitbucket.org/pypa/setuptools/issue/65
https://bitbucket.org/cffi/cffi/issue/139/

Change-Id: I166aa679bcec79afdaf013b8f393957f849d4daf

commit_message:
Correct the return of diagnosing stopped instance

When diagnosing a stopped instance, the nova CLI return a incorrect
message.
It should return nothing to confirm to nova API.

Change-Id: I59b28193e5731089ebb8bc2c9a53bbc8b43155e3
Closes-bug: #1289079

commit_message:
Run hacking and flake checks for real

Previous tox configuration didn't run any of hacking or flake8 checks. This
commit enables both. Here are details:
* Added hacking to test-requirements. It'll manage it's own dependencies -
  pep8, pyflakes, and flake8
* Enabled flake8
* Disabled a bunch of hacking and flake rules. They should be fixed in next
  dependend patches
* Removed unused test dependency - pysendfiles

Change-Id: I8dcbd4da6d0ced7e9f6a5a760020cbefa62657e9

commit_message:
Replace more then just "-" in REPONAME

Looks like shells only support alphanumeric characters and "_"'s in
environment variables. We were substituting "-" characters but in
order to be able to set overrides in projects with names containing
other characters we need to substitute more, I'm looking at you
oslo.config.

Change-Id: I3e2b1b0bc5871e4ec4ffd8117906cd077aa2cb0d
Co-authored-by: James Polley <jp@jamezpolley.com>

commit_message:
Modify timeout in client shell

this parameter is not only available in creation,
but also update and deletion.

- use '-t' '--timeout' to set this parameter in shell
- modify parameter document

Change-Id: I8ec3c63e9de2c650e9018ad93562159a064e9356

commit_message:
Fix comparison with singletons in unit tests

Several places in the code use assertEqual(None, x) or
assertNotEqual(None, x).

As comparison to singletons must use `is` operator, appropriate usage
was changed to assertIsNone, assertIsNotNone

Change-Id: I7188f178d6db4dc4314860961d51e35447ed59c4

commit_message:
N1kv: Fixes fields argument not None

N1kv plugin includes 'fields' in call to get_<resource> function in
superclass. This can trigger errors if other fields are used in the
subsequent processing in the N1kv plugin's own get_<resource>
function.

Change-Id: I63687a830579a178c6daaa2b8f71bef7eb53d584
Closes-bug: #1285289

commit_message:
the check for status.status should happen before trying to log it

otherwise, if status.status is None, status.status.api_status will throw
a TypeError

Closes-Bug: #1287097
Change-Id: I62dafed59dcf8850808b22b8977d346607176403

Hi Vincent, sorry for not noticing the earlier comments from John on patch set 2 and not clarifying this earlier. When the vmdk driver APIs are being called on a volume whose backing vmdk does not exist yet, it is not an error condition in most cases (at least until now). For example when trying to create a volume from another source volume that does not yet exist, obviously the user wants to copy over only the meta data from the source volume. This is how the driver is currently implemented. I understand that this is counter intuitive to how other drivers are implemented but we should not be breaking this model without diligence.

In your fix you have raised exceptions in all these cases. This breaks the driver badly. This would lead to the operation failing and leaving the volume in an 'error' state. So kindly revert these exceptions."}, {'account_id': 2861, 'date': '2014-01-24 01:37:19.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 6:

I have the same question from the previous review. https://review.openstack.org/#/c/59924/25 How does this adjust quotas if it's not going through the manager?"}, {'account_id': 2861, 'date': '2014-02-08 13:33:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 15:

There is no need to adjust the quota here after the volume extends, because the quota is reserved correctly, and the issue is the VMDK datastore does not allocate the right volume size. If we copy an image of 1G into a volume of 2G, the quota can reserve and commit this 2G, because this value comes from the user input. In this issue, the quota reservation and commit have the correct value, but the backend VMDK datastore allocates 1G instead of 2G, because the datastore reads the size of the image, not the user input size. It is the backend that makes the mistake. I resize the volume in the end just to make sure that the backend datastore allocates the RIGHT size as the quota reserves and commits.'}, {'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2014-02-08 17:04:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 15:

Hey Vincent,
It took me a while to understand what was going on here.  It's not very clear "which" volume is being used extended.  I had the same concern as Mike and actually was going to -2 because of auto-extend.  Looking closer though I noticed the extend is actually only taking place on the backend vmdk file.

The extend isn't actually being performed on a Cinder object.  Maybe it would be good to add some more details around how this works via comments in the code since I'm seemingly not the only person that was confused by this.'}, {'account_id': 2861, 'date': '2014-02-10 02:33:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 15:

commit_message:
VMware: Take the volume size from the user input

When we create a volume from an image or a snapshot, we need to
take the size of the volume from the user input and validate whether
the size is appropriate instead of taking the image size as the
volume size directly.

Change-Id: If09933d8ffa989c4dacc0860c19ea332bc21092a
Closes-Bug: #1237557

hi Liang Chen,
  there is also another reson,you can see bp/stack-convergence,heat will know the changes of underlying resources,for examplae,if you suspend a server in nova,heat will set it in suspended state.And from the code already have,heat seems care litte about state on stack level.a lot of checking is on resource level.'}, {'account_id': 7135, 'date': '2014-03-05 08:18:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Hi Zhang Yang,

commit_message:
Add state check when suspend or resume stack

If suspend a stack which is already suspended,
some resource will throw exceptions.and you can't
suspend or resume that failed resource.

Add stack check when update or resume,if the
state of stack is expecter,return directly.

Change-Id: Ie6859c03168d9d18e88bbeb6df2c646541f2aa9d
Closes-Bug: 1284531

commit_message:
Increases timeout for guest agent resize_fs

When the guest agent resizes the file system, it may take longer
than the AGENT_LOW_TIMEOUT and should use AGENT_HIGH_TIMEOUT to
ensure the resize has sufficient time to complete.

Change-Id: Ic3c030f60ca47d894eb25b83f05b63ef22d519f8
Closes-Bug: #1288766

[{'created': '2014-03-11 00:35:37.000000000', 'message': "Account for stack_user_project_id in stack_get_by_name

stack_get compares the context tenant to the stack tenant
and the stack_user_project_id. stack_get_by_name only filters
by tenant, so identify_stack fails when looking up by stack name
and the stack_user_project_id is the context tenant (such as when
there is a cfn API describe resource call).

This change searches for tenant or stack_user_project_id for
stack_get_by_name and stack_get_by_name_and_owner_id. It also
extends the tests to ensure a stack is returned when
stack_user_project_id matches, and no stack is returned when
tenant doesn't match.

Closes-Bug: #1288523
Change-Id: I875e232a791c71a4ad55a0e4e5a1423ec3546119
"}]
commit_message:
Account for stack_user_project_id in stack_get_by_name

stack_get compares the context tenant to the stack tenant
and the stack_user_project_id. stack_get_by_name only filters
by tenant, so identify_stack fails when looking up by stack name
and the stack_user_project_id is the context tenant (such as when
there is a cfn API describe resource call).

This change searches for tenant or stack_user_project_id for
stack_get_by_name and stack_get_by_name_and_owner_id. It also
extends the tests to ensure a stack is returned when
stack_user_project_id matches, and no stack is returned when
tenant doesn't match.

Closes-Bug: #1288523
Change-Id: I875e232a791c71a4ad55a0e4e5a1423ec3546119

commit_message:
Call an existing method in sync cache for revoke events

The cache used for synchronizing the revocation tree across
green threads had an issue where it was calling a non-existant
method ``remove`` instead of ``remove_event``. The correct method
is now being called and an expanded test to exercise the synchronize
method has been added.

Change-Id: I3fe47fa51f88aab89480831b2d95746319f82ceb
Closes-Bug: 1289935

 * Update oslo log messages with translation domains

commit_message:
Update oslo-incubator db.sqlalchemy module

Changes -
 * Add from_config() method to EngineFacade
 * Introduce mysql_sql_mode option, remove old warning
 * Introduce a method to set any MySQL session SQL mode
 * Handle ibm_db_sa DBDuplicateEntry integrity errors
 * Fix migration.db_version when no tables
 * Update log translation domains
 * Add model_query() to db.sqlalchemy.utils module
 * Remove None for dict.get()
 * Fix duplicating of SQL queries in logs
 * Update oslo log messages with translation domains

Change-Id: I654acad217e552e64283e93ef884d5cd8dea58da

commit_message:
Show the service id for service-list command

Current service-list command does not show each service id.
Nova contains a RESTful API to delete a service with the specified id.
This patch adds the service id column to use the id in the above case.

Change-Id: I616573c6d5b7e922a6c79d92752a19f65cca00d5

commit_message:
Use multiprocessing in UserGenerator for creating tenants and users.

Create each tenant and its users in separate process to save performance.

Notes:
  * single keystone client is used for each process
  * tenants IDs and users IDs are saved in UserGenerator instance instead of their instances,
    to avoid keystone client manager issue (recursion is caused by keystoneclient.base.Resource.__getattr__)

Blueprint conrurrent-creation-of-users

Change-Id: I484a9351c53c98a33712d19d28c651535e637e47

commit_message:
Ensure localcontext can be monkeypatched

_STORE must be instanciated at first use, not at module loading time,
to ensure eventlet can monkeypatch the threading module before the
creation of the threading.local() object

Closes-bug: #1288878

commit_message:
Fixed _error_checker in rest client

Restclient's method '_error_checker' for response codes 500 and 501 gets key
error exception when 'resp_body' is a string and passes conditions for
containing of keys.
Also added fix to rarely raised Exceptions after separation main and base
exceptions for two modules.

Closes-Bug: #1280767
Closes-Bug: #1289190
Partially-implements: bp unit-tests
Change-Id: I4b909d008940f8a96efc922daac64a086819c78a

commit_message:
Handle not found exceptions in update_floatingip_status()

Update_status may come from agent on a floating ip which was
already deleted from db - need to handle such cases properly

Change-Id: Idfa240f8dcb0a2e5c2a97b0f168bf1ba2d7dc50f
Closes-Bug: #1287049

commit_message:
Fix state modifying catalog tests

Some of the service catalog tests modify the global state. They should
take a copy of the dictionary before modifying it.

Change-Id: I5de52949d561322958f603022af893f087c55e03

commit_message:
Remove unused build_url function in data_utils

This commit removes build_url function in data_utils because there is no
user of this code. The using code of this function was removed at
 I1102859c871b8f16c284bdf7fba0f4346d50a63e .

commit_message:
rename and fix the db_wipe command

* rename db_wipe to db_recreate
* make --repo-path an optional argument for db_wipe and use it
* add command line help strings for db_wipe

Closes-Bug: #1279734

Change-Id: I1a1d3ad56989026fb10f6c57bb479814dc51328e

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-03-06 02:48:10.000000000', 'message': 'Fix for boolean configuration parameters

Issues:
Boolean configuration parameters are treated as integers and have to
specify min(0)/max(1) values for boolean params.
If cli -> trove configuration-create configparams '{"logappend":false}',
then cli -> trove show <configuration>, would still print it as cli ->
values | {u'logappend': False}. False instead of false.
This is due to Python upcasing booleans. Expected behavior is it should
print boolean params as true/false instead of True/False.

Fixes:
This change fixes the above mentioned issues.

Closes-Bug: #1288507
Change-Id: I2d7556621e891b22291c7ef9e9c523e1ce98a047
'}, {'created': '2014-03-10 03:55:13.000000000', 'message': 'Remove Min/Max for Configuration Group Booleans

boolean configuration-group parameters at the moment require a
min/max value of 0/1 to work around some faulty logic that is
meant to validate integer values, but instead validates integer
and boolean values.

Closes-Bug: #1288507
Change-Id: I2d7556621e891b22291c7ef9e9c523e1ce98a047
'}]
commit_message:
Remove Min/Max for Configuration Group Booleans

boolean configuration-group parameters at the moment require a
min/max value of 0/1 to work around some faulty logic that is
meant to validate integer values, but instead validates integer
and boolean values.

Closes-Bug: #1288507
Change-Id: I2d7556621e891b22291c7ef9e9c523e1ce98a047

devops node to nailgun node.

commit_message:
Fix context serialization in Execution.create

Proper serialization for context passed as dict.

Also:
 * fix type casting in Exception message

Closes-Bug: #1290214

commit_message:
Fixed backup unittests to use mocked cmd

The backup unittests were using the actual cmd from the backup
implementation (eg. innobackupex) instead of the faked unit test
cmd. Fixed this so that calls to innobackupex are no longer being
made when running the unit tests.

Closes-bug: 1290290
Change-Id: I26b77efbf95feb5a32777197c7cba08f7b757c38

commit_message:
Make functions in manila uniquenamed

Manila's devstack plugin has samenamed functions as in
cinder. It makes problems using cinder with manila's installation.
All function names should be unique.

Change-Id: I32fa7aecc7b74692b60c040cabd371f1499c21e6
Closes-Bug: #1290552

commit_message:
Modify API tests to check the calls

Since often mocked response is returned untouched by the tested
function, we need to check not only that it returns the proper
response, but also that it makes a right request too.

Change-Id: I87bf79d9c8648f8377c0c27b1cd4992a6e5af598
Closes-Bug: #1288169

Renat, to find an answer to your question, you need to ask yourself why do we need to create a loop with time.sleep at the end (https://review.openstack.org/gitweb?p=stackforge/mistral.git;a=blob;f=mistral/tests/unit/engine/scalable/test_executor.py;h=d55041e8f2a5d66359f1ab0ad79b89d2931cebaa;hb=b94f45f870ee12f2b8bff658225a55e6d7d946c6#l165). 

As i understand it, the reason here is that task won't be executed immediately, instead FakeDriver will imitate (I'm not sure how exactly) the lag that happens when you are working with message queue.

As far as i can tell, we would have to make such a loop  every time we launch new task."}, {'account_id': 8731, 'date': '2014-03-11 06:34:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Ok, Kirill. I now see what you're saying. I'm sure we'll find a solution to avoid that sleep thing (which is ugly, I agree).. In my understanding we should be able to build a future object for a given execution when we start a workflow to block on it till the workflow has finished. Btw, this is sort of an event listener that we postponed, it would solve a problem easily here."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-03-11 06:42:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: No score

commit_message:
Use oslo.messaging for AMQP communications

Ported task executor to oslo.messaging. The executor module is
replaced with RPC server/client named Executor and ExecutorClient
respectively to handle task execution. The old executor module is
deleted.  The engine is modified to use the ExecutorClient to send
task requests over the transport to the Executor. The launcher is
modified to start the new Executor.

Change-Id: Ibce01813e51c2220c45e05bb820b4729027446a3
Implements: blueprint mistral-oslo-messaging

commit_message:
Fixed creation of cinder's volumes

Manila's function "_configure_tgt_for_config_d"
was imported second and was redefining cinder's
with same name. It caused absense of cinder.conf for
tgt.

Change-Id: I259994b337f857a3f71a37f91e71bbe2543d0815
Closes-Bug: #1290516

commit_message:
Instances are not stuck in BACKUP

Fixed the backup running states, so that a NEW state is no longer
considered running. This means that Instances are not stuck in
BACKUP unless they are actively performing a backup.

Closes-bug: 1252897
Change-Id: Ia9be9f19d695a66bcc2a9b952584139652d97773

commit_message:
Hard disable config drive to test file injection

DO NOT MERGE. This is a test of the test system :). This commit hard
disables config drive forcing file injection to be used instead to see
if file injection is broken everywhere.

Test if libguestfs documentation indicates the proper way to fix
libguestfs on precise.

Change-Id: Iab4d59df24770b402f74ab8591a7ff5ea1a3b3bc

commit_message:
Implement pluggability for tempest (clients)

Third patch of three patches:
  1. exceptions
  2. config (+ module_utils.py)
->3. clients

It is very useful for new projects, who can just place
needed files into appropriate dirs without changing
tempest core files.
Much less merge conflicts and separation of base classes and
child classes.

Partially-implements: bp make-tempest-pluggable

Change-Id: Ib4f5b7004d86a4a194a7bd93905d6b7b12e07801

commit_message:
Add "list fping servers" tests for Nova V2 api

This commit adds tests for Nova V2 API:
    'GET os-fping'
NOTE: This API is only in Nova V2. So we don't need this for Nova V3.

Change-Id: Ie3c9279132900db28dc0362c01955097e01147b7

commit_message:
Add -N option to force using the local environment

Add the -N option to force using the local environement and not creating
a new virtualenv. Unlike other OpenStack project this option is default
in heat, we add it to match what other projects are doing and make it
easier to maintain integration scripts for packagers.

Partial-Bug: #1273598
Change-Id: I3b84613ef30926a1dd5e979278a615c0f11c0cde

commit_message:
VPNaaS integration with service type framework

* adds new attribute 'provider' for vpnservice
* adds support for multiple drivers for vpn

Implements blueprint vpn-service-types-integration
DocImpact

Change-Id: I9e195dfaee21b1cf204cb9b9fc773bc9e5af5936

commit_message:
resource-list fails on a stack with ResourceGroup

The ResourceGroup does not have nested resources. This causes a
an AttributeError when doing a resource-list.

Co-Authored-By: Keith Bray <keith.bray@rackspace.com>
Change-Id: I5428f4ea9e935b29a81f9a9cd8e7536d427f4cce
Closes-Bug: #1280391

commit_message:
Add APIv3 support to make host optional on evacuate.

In the event of an unrecoverable hardware failure, support needs to
relocate an instance to another compute so it can be rebuilt.
  [*] Bump v3 version of evacuate to set host argument optional.

DocImpact: The evacuate target host is now optional. If
'host' field is not sent in the request, the scheduler
will determine the target host. This will include
nova client changes ( on the proper commit ) to support
this new optional parameter.

Implements: blueprint find-host-and-evacuate-instance

Change-Id: I787853dcb6ba4e57a5726752a66487ef4472b01f
Co-Authored-By: Juan M. Olle <juan.m.olle@intel.com>
Co-Authored-By: Andres Buraschi <andres.buraschi@intel.com>
Co-Authored-By: Anuj Mathur <anujm@thoughtworks.com>
Co-Authored-By: Navneet Kumar <navneetk@thoughtworks.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claxton Correya <claxton@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Add flake8 to run_tests.sh

Devstack has not only shell scripts but also some python tools in the
tools directory. So we should check whether the code keeps the pep8
rules automatically.

Change-Id: I2d27eda0dd8551289dc4ad7c7652101ba235b987

Add rabbit.cookie attribute

All nodes in rabbitmq cluster should have same cookie. This patch adds
default random cookie to existing templates.

commit_message:
Handle options not registered on module import

Try to discover and include options that are not registered on module import but
when actually executing the code.

We find calls to register_opts() that cannot be handled on import, extract the
arguments and explicitly call register_opt() to make oslo.config aware of them.

Change-Id: I4566b68b59d5a7a1e15cbd3fb9fcec1a51f9abac

commit_message:
Stop using generator._list_opts; use cfg.CONF instead

We don't use the information about defining module anywhere. Using
that routine just makes the code slower and causes crashes in Neutron
and possibly elsewhere whenever an option is defined in the top level
but not registered.

Change-Id: I946c740cd0ce6fa5d969964d79a75a406e8453ab

Isn't this already a pep8 check?"}, {'account_id': 4146, 'date': '2014-03-04 18:10:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

It isn't already a pep8 check. pep8 ensures you have:

  code  #foo

This change makes you do:

  code  # foo

Which seems to be inconsistent because this change allows #TODO and #NOTE and #FIXME. Consistency is more important here imo.

What is the motivation for this change?"}, {'account_id': 4, 'date': '2014-03-04 18:12:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

jeblair: PEP8 has "E261 at least two spaces before inline comment", but not quite this.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-03-04 18:33:39.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Doesn't seem to work

Build failed.  For information on how to proceed, see https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/GerritJenkinsGit#Test_Failures

- gate-hacking-pep8 http://logs.openstack.org/50/77950/2/check/gate-hacking-pep8/dabd500 : FAILURE in 50s

"}, {'account_id': 4, 'date': '2014-03-04 18:52:00.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

@clark: the motivation is simply consistency in favor of the prevailing (and I'd argue: easier to read) style.

On that note, I'd rather support for #TODO and #NOTE and #FIXME dropped in favor of # TODO and # NOTE and # FIXME as part of this change, if that's possible."}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2014-03-04 19:38:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Do not merge

"An inline comment is a comment on the same line as a statement. Inline comments should be separated by at least two spaces from the statement. They should start with a # and a single space." http://legacy.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008/

It sounds like this should be enforced upstream in pep8, since its a pep8 rule.'}, {'account_id': 4, 'date': '2014-03-04 20:42:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

"They should start with a # and a single space." that's not enforced upstream, so why not enforce it here?'}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2014-03-04 20:50:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Because pep8 enforces pep8, and hacking is for hacking.'}, {'account_id': 5046, 'date': '2014-03-11 05:23:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
put libvirt debug in the right place

libvirt debug setting was happening in a place where we weren't
actually resetting the daemon. Move it to into the hypervisor
plugin where we do.

Change-Id: Ia79b0ef50f6b8fb007a20ce5cb4e510a5e4600a5

commit_message:
Prepare for enabling H302 rule (api/compute/admin)

We can use H302 rule but ignore it now. This commit prepares for
enabling H302 rule. But this commit modifies a part of Tempest only
because if we fix all of them at one time, it's hard to merge this
commit.

    ---------------
    tempest/api/compute/admin     <- This patch
    tempest/api/compute/{c*,f*,i*,s*,t*}
    tempest/api/compute/{v3,volumes},data_processing
    tempest/api/identity/admin
    tempest/api/image
    tempest/api/{n*,o*,t*}
    tempest/api/volume,tempest/*
    tempest/services/compute/json
    tempest/services/compute/v3/json
    tempest/services/compute/xml
    tempest/services/identity
    tempest/services/{im*,n*,o*,t*}
    tempest/services/volume
    tempest/clients.py: TBD
    ---------------

Change-Id: Id993c8b157c0b1256aa17c2b8e8f8da46111c521

commit_message:
xenapi: fix spawn servers with ephemeral disks

The new resize ephemeral disk code uses vdis["ephemerals"] to pass the
list of ephemeral vdis to the resize disk code. This is shared between
spawn and resize. As spawn wants to resize the root disk, resize=True
during the spawn operation.

The code in _attach_disks correctly deals with empty ephemeral disks,
but the code in _resize_up_vdis did not, and failed due to
ephemeral_vdis being None.

This is a quick fix for the issue. We need some refactoring in this area
so there is, ideally, only one place that generates ephemeral disks.

Change-Id: If058c5c17c2ed76569fd98d4a3d8e5274721fbd0
Closes-Bug: #1289361

Fix the argument indents of flavors_extraspecs

952a26a851ed11d157dba926349472cdac00155b has used db.flavor_ instead
of db.instance_type_ but it has not fitted the argument indents.

commit_message:
Fix lack of extended port's attributes in Metaplugin

Previously, there are some extended port's attributes did not
appear in the result of GET port API when using Metaplugin.
This become a critial issue currently since lack of port binding
information disturbs normal port binding operation in a compute
node, for example.

Metaplugin did not delegate get_port/get_ports to target plugins.
This is cause of the problem because right plugin instance is not
passed to a hook which handles extended attributes.
Now, get_port/get_ports of target plugins are called so that
extended port's attributes are handled properly.

Change-Id: Ifed2505a97ceca56c4cedd22efa49adcdf3317b8
Closes-Bug: #1136252

commit_message:
Add App Detail page

This patch added a new App Details page to App Catalog.
Right now it uses fake model application but
UI render part is complete.
There is no error handling here yet, it should be
added later.
The main purpose of this prototype is to define
an API methods we will need to render UI.
This stuff do not cover Icons yet.

Change-Id: I6ae9f76ac9db88e7918a1fa5add5632b0865985f

commit_message:
Fix setup_test_v3_user method in identity base.py

Create user in v3 identity json/xml only has two parameters.
To test the fixing, I add a v3 user test :
- test_get_user

Change-Id: I2168a21f361e0ed83b91de06652bfeea424f92f6

commit_message:
Add tiles view for App Catalog

This patch adds a main view for App Catalog.
This is a first draft of App Catalog page based
on tiles approach. App Catalog page has two
sections:
Latest Apps - the newest? or probably last used by his user
App List a list of apps with pagination and category filter.

Change-Id: I70d2ab25bfc13a0aa410f808aaac11050db38242

security_groups test scripts of compute.

commit_message:
Stress runner friendly logging.conf.sample

tempest.common.log.TestsFormatter formatter was removed from the tempest
repository. It makes the current sample config file useless.
We will use the same ContextFormatter in the sample config as we use in the
normal runs.

The tempest.log file will be appended, instead of replacing.
The summary of the stress runs will be printed to the stdout.

The syslog handler preserved in the sample config, but it is not in use
anymore. If someone want to use, he can enable it by little change.

NOTE:
You need change tempest.conf [DEFAULT]/log_config_append to point a valid
logging config, if you would like to use special log related
configuration.

Change-Id: Ic6ede3943e309a102d4af6dec505f0d4cbd3bc2b

commit_message:
Provide attribute schema for waitcondition resource

Provide the waitcondition resource with an attribute schema defining
the Data attribute, so it will show up in the template guide docs.

Closes-Bug: #1280268

Change-Id: I8bcbd4b6795d4ca682ed933de437164675f66dc7

commit_message:
Add Images for App Catalog

This patch adds some logic around image handling.
Added images for app entries and details page.
Added image caching logic to store images on local disk.
Added Content-Cache header to cache images on client side too.

Change-Id: I34983311d3e53c54e00118609f5944f0971df507

commit_message:
Use debug level logging during unit tests

When unit tests fail we need to debug, so we should have debug level logging on.
We use fixtures FakeLogger during testing, to  enable debug logging pass
in log level as a parameter.
http://bazaar.launchpad.net/~python-fixtures/python-fixtures/trunk/view/head:/lib/fixtures/_fixtures/logger.py#L68

Change-Id: I70790aa39c0774726de71e5fa5751c45e7e34ffd
